  "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
  "body": "*Description*:\r\nWe're in process of deploying Envoy and we've noticed the presence of max limit for zone/endpoint weight.\r\nWe have a need to send only a small fraction of traffic (\u22480.0001) to some zones.\r\nExamples are: validating that some zone is dead/alive, or checking if passive zone doesn't drop traffic on the floor for failover-like scenarios.\r\n\r\nBased on the prior discussions (https://github.com/envoyproxy/envoy/issues/1285) it looks like this limit is not useful anymore for WRR/Least Loaded load balancing policies.\r\nIf there are no other concerns, can it be just removed? \r\n\r\n*Relevant Links*:\r\n* https://github.com/envoyproxy/envoy/issues/1285\r\n* https://github.com/envoyproxy/envoy/blob/9b096c31d36ee908888c071d2073d126693dc3c0/api/envoy/api/v2/endpoint/endpoint.proto#L85-L92\r\n* https://github.com/envoyproxy/envoy/blob/9b096c31d36ee908888c071d2073d126693dc3c0/api/envoy/api/v2/endpoint/endpoint.proto#L117-L123",
